== Description ==

The '''BIM ImagePlane''' tool creates a planar object from an image file. The image is mapped onto a rectangular plane in the [[3D_View|3D View]], allowing you to use reference images (such as floor plans, elevations, or sketches) as visual guides during BIM modeling.

== Usage ==

# Select the {{MenuCommand|Utils → [[Image:BIM_ImagePlane.svg|16px]] Image Plane}} option from the menu.
# A file dialog opens.
# Select an image file (PNG, JPG, or BMP).
# Click two points in the [[3D_view|3D View]] to define the diagonal corners of the Image Plane.
# An Image Plane is created, fitted to the aspect ratio of the original image.

== Notes ==

* You can edit an Image Plane as described [[Std_Import#Edit|here]]. The size and position of an Image Plane can also be adjusted with the [[Draft_Move|Draft Move]] and [[Draft_Scale|Draft Scale]] tools.


